#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat <<'EOF'
webmin-node — install and operate a Webmin web administration service

COMMANDS
  version            Print the package version
  daemon install     Add the official repo and install webmin
  daemon enable      Enable the boot service
  daemon start       Start the webmin service
  daemon stop        Stop the webmin service
  daemon restart     Restart the webmin service
  daemon status      Check whether webmin is running
  daemon monitor     Tail the miniserv log
  daemon disable     Stop and disable the service

USAGE
  webmin-node daemon install
  webmin-node daemon enable && webmin-node daemon start
  # then open https://127.0.0.1:10000

WEBMIN PROVIDES
  - Browser-based system administration (users, groups, cron, packages)
  - Service, firewall, network, and disk management
  - Module UIs for Apache, BIND, MySQL/PostgreSQL, Samba, and more

RUNS AS ROOT
  Webmin administers the host, so it runs as root (no dedicated service
  account). Restrict access with the firewall and/or miniserv.conf
  'allow=' rules; put a reverse proxy in front for a public hostname.

SERVICES
  Web UI:  https://127.0.0.1:10000

FILES
  Binary/libs:  /usr/share/webmin
  Config:       /etc/webmin/ (miniserv.conf, miniserv.users)
  Logs:         /var/log/webmin/miniserv.log

PLATFORM
  Linux only (apt/dnf). macOS is not packaged by this node.

SETUP
  1. Install:        webmin-node daemon install
  2. Enable + start: webmin-node daemon enable && webmin-node daemon start
  3. Log in:         https://<host>:10000 as a root/sudo user

SEE ALSO
  webmin-node-daemon(1)
  https://www.webmin.com/
EOF
